  "id": 6323071520735232,
  "name": "Support rect() and xywh() in shape-outside",
  "summary": "Adds support for the rect() and xywh() basic shape functions in the CSS shape-outside property. These functions allow developers to define float exclusion shapes using rectangle coordinates, aligning Chrome with Firefox and Safari which already support this feature.",
